Text.Value: Have you retrieved the Orphic Hammer? Will our prince's chains finally be broken?
Leave.
Even if you could, you would relinquish your mind to the elder brain in so doing.
A silver sword.
Have you retrieved the Orphic Hammer? Will our prince's chains finally be broken?
Have you brought the Orphic Hammer?
The remaining honour guard serve as my eyes and ears.
Find a way into the Astral Prism and use the Orphic Hammer to free the True Heir.
He must keep the Orphic Hammer there.
Not a new companion, but an old one - and a loyal one.
Getting into the Astral Prism will be complicated.
The prophecy is one step closer to fruition.
Think again. I will not permit your entry.
The House of Hope. We must find a way in.
Vlaakith's forces hunt you and the Prism. My allies have slayed more than you know, so that you might travel freely.
He might seethe when you free him. He might gnash his teeth and slander your name.
The Prince of the Comet will sear the heavens again. First we'll defeat the Absolute. Then we let the lich queen tremble!
The Prince of the Comet aches for githyanki liberation more than he abhors ghaik.
You need to let me into the Prism.
Any idea where I might find the Hammer?
No, there is not.
But he will see reason. I promise you.
Orpheus sensed the tadpole before, and his guard attacked. Won't he attack if we free him?
Is there any way I can convince you?
T'lak'ma Ghir, now that you have the Hammer you must find a way to enter the Astral Prism.
Vin'iisk, now that you have the Hammer you must find a way to enter the Astral Prism.
Istik, now that you have the Hammer you must find a way to enter the Astral Prism.
I've retrieved the Hammer.
I've retrieved the Hammer.
And may your mind be of steel so your blade may be of silver, T'lak'ma Ghir.
Leave.
Where are the rest of your allies?

'The Prince of the Comet is not dead.
The Prince of the Comet will come again.
The Prince of the Comet will liberate us from the lich queen's tyranny.'
Then I will wait here until you have. The chains that bind Orpheus also bind the whole of our people.
Then I will wait here until you have. The chains that bind Orpheus also bind the whole of the githyanki people.
I'll find a way to free Orpheus from your clutches.
A proper introduction is in order. But I will let him do the honours.
I haven't recovered the Hammer just yet.
The House of Hope, you say? I couldn't ask for a name more fitting.
Questions, Lae'zel? You seem to be lost in thought.
Questions, vin'iisk? You seem to be lost in thought.
Questions, istik? You seem to be lost in thought.
And you will wield the greatest gift Mother Gith ever granted her dauntless children.

Text.Value: Ignore the Emperor.
Kith'rak Voss. May the Astral Sea be still as you cross it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Just an aphorism, as in 'May the road rise up to meet you.'

Text.Value: No, I do not.
I'm here for your head, traitor.
Among our people, one gift is esteemed above all others. The silver sword.
Among the githyanki, one gift is esteemed above all others. The silver sword.

EditorData.logicalname: Lae'zel did not intervene, Voss has Sword

Text.Value: A devil of Raphael's stature does not simply make camp on the shores of the Styx.
Gith's son will soon ride against Vlaakith, Voss. And I will follow him into battle.
Yes. But you will meet this challenge, as you've met so many others.
When I am done with the gith princeling, you may do with him as you like. But not a moment before.
Orpheus' cry will shake the planes, and I will fly to your side.
Lae'zel, T'lak'ma Ghir. May your mind be of steel, so your blade may be of silver.
Ah - you've finally come.
Once inside, smash Orpheus' bonds. His cry will shake the planes, and I will fly to your aid.
Take it. Wield it in honour of Gith, the great liberator - and her unforgotten son.

Text.Value: Every house has an entrance, Lae'zel - even those in the Hells. A diabolist in this very city might know the way.
Every house has an entrance, vin'iisk - even those in the Hells. A diabolist in this very city might know the way.
Every house has an entrance, istik - even those in the Hells. A diabolist in this very city might know the way.
I will carry it for the honour of Gith, the great liberator - and her unforgotten son.
As for those that break through, you've proven more than capable of bleeding them yourself.
He will have made a sanctuary for himself. A lavish one, too, one that caters to his many vices.
Lae'zel, sister in freedom. Together, we will end the elder brain which shakes this city. Then, we turn our sights to Vlaakith, the queen of deceit.
Vin'iisk, friend to Orpheus. Together, we will end the elder brain which shakes this city. Then, we turn our sights to Vlaakith, the queen of deceit.
Istik, friend to Orpheus. Together, we will end the elder brain which shakes this city. Then, I turn my sights to Vlaakith, the queen of deceit.
A new companion, I see. You've partnered with my kind.
Who is this new companion of yours?

Synopsis:
Voss waits in the sewers until you get the hammer. Then he's there with the dragon he rode in Act1 in humanoid form. If you show him the hammer then, he rewards you with a Silver Sword and then leaves to meet you in endgame.

He will still be in endgame even if you didn't do this step, but you just would have missed on the Silver Sword.
